Rating: 4
I can't believe how easy this was and how delicious it turned out! Few modifications - threw in one Idaho potato along with the rutabaga and sweet potatoes, and used 4 cups of chicken broth + 1 cup water as the base. Didn't need to add salt. Served with chewy whole wheat baguette - perfect!

Rating: 4
Very good, and I am especially fond of rutabagas. I used the chicken broth, a couple of white potatoes and stirred cream in at the end. I also pureed only about half of the soup and added it right back to the lumpy stuff. Great texture and preserves some of the individual flavors. I recommend it.

