This was easy to make, but the taste didn't suit me. The soup was a little too sweet for my liking.

Rating: 3
Yummy and easy; have made three times. Since we don't eat red meat, we substituted turkey bacon. The soup had a very strong bacon flavor but was quite delicious. We didn't add cream (or any dairy) or use chicken broth instead of water. Our kids loved it too; will definitely make again and again.

Rating: 2
This was very good. I wasn't so sure if I was going to like it once I started cooking. I used chicken broth and cream and believe they are necessary. I also feel that the bacon served on top really made it.

Rating: 4
Delicious! I used the comments from other cooks and included both chicken broth and a little cream in my recipe. Also included the potato and turnip. Just before serving, I added a dollop of sour cream to each bowl and then sprinkled the bacon on. Loved it. My sister went back for seconds. Freezed the leftovers for later.

Rating: 3
I couldn't find rutabaga in my market - I guess it's the wrong time of the year, so I used yellow turnip as this was suggested to be close by the Epicurious Dictionary. I used low-salt bacon wich left the soup needing salt. Overall, it was a nice soup that is just too easy and straight forward to not try to make again. I'll keep my eyes out for rutabaga but the turnip was pretty good.

